isAsynchronousWrite

public boolean isAsynchronousWrite
True if you want to write file asynchronously. You can define the number of thread dedicate to write file in FactoryCsvWriter. By default the number of processor divide by 3. If you create several files in the same time, the threads will be share for each files.

Since:
0.0.1

header

public java.lang.String header
the header of CSV file generated. The header is generated with the name of field. If no name is defined for a field, we take the property name or method name

Since:
0.0.1

filename

public java.lang.String filename

You can define a static file name.

Since:
0.0.1

isAppendToFile

public boolean isAppendToFile

True if you want to append csv data to a file (if it exist). If the file doesn't exist, it create a new file.

False, if you already want to create a new file. By default, it's false.

Since:
0.0.1
